ObjectDetection - Class in org.lasarobotics.vision.detection
Object Detector - searches a scene for keypoints then can match keypoints in the object to keypoints in the scene, effectively locating an object within a scene

This class is designed to detect a single object at a time in an image

ObjectDetection() - Constructor for class org.lasarobotics.vision.detection.ObjectDetection
Instantiate an object detector based on the FAST, BRIEF, and BRUTEFORCE_HAMMING algorithms
ObjectDetection(ObjectDetection.FeatureDetectorType, ObjectDetection.DescriptorExtractorType, ObjectDetection.DescriptorMatcherType) - Constructor for class org.lasarobotics.vision.detection.ObjectDetection
Instantiate an object detector based on custom algorithms
ObjectDetection.DescriptorExtractorType - Enum in org.lasarobotics.vision.detection
Descriptor extractor types

Descriptor extractors get information from the feature detector and analyze it in various ways - these descriptors are then stored in the object analysis to later search for the same descriptors in the scene.

ObjectDetection.DescriptorMatcherType - Enum in org.lasarobotics.vision.detection
Descriptor matcher types

Descriptor matchers match descriptors found from the object to descriptors in an image - they effectively locate the object in the scene.

ObjectDetection.FeatureDetectorType - Enum in org.lasarobotics.vision.detection
Feature detector types

Feature detectors search the images for features - typically corners - that are then extracted and processed to locate an object in a scene.

ObjectDetection.ObjectAnalysis - Class in org.lasarobotics.vision.detection

ObjectDetection.SceneAnalysis - Class in org.lasarobotics.vision.detection
